              <span slot="content">The epic conclusion to the trilogy! This one has always stood apart from the other 2 in my opinion because, not only does this movie wrap up the story arcs of characters we’ve known and followed for 2 movies, it does so while bathing the camera in the orange hues of the old west. It really sets this movie apart from 80s pop, flying cars, and 50s high school dances by making a transition to a Western with underlying tension regarding getting home to 1985. This movie also makes one big improvement from the first 2. In the first 2 movies, Marty is the definitive main character. But in Part III, Doc gets more time to shine. The focus on the characters feels much more balanced in this movie, with there being an almost equal focus on Marty and Doc (maybe even a little more to Doc’s side). His story with Clara was also sweet and added an extra element of romance to the film. Great movie on its own and also an amazing conclusion to this amazing trilogy!</span>
            </drawer-more>
